<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-09-23T21:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-09-23T21:00:00-05:00" n="376" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d376">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/24355:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Consul General at Algiers (<persName type="to">Cole</persName>)</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-09-23T22:00:00-04:00">September 23, 1942—10 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>287. From Murphy. Your 616, September 19, 11 a.m. Please advise Saint
                                that this information is useful and that we would like any
                                additional data he may obtain regarding Noguès’ present visit to
                                Vichy.</p>
                            <p>Any effort which can be made tactfully to ridicule the rumors of an
                                American landing would be appreciated. [Murphy.]</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>